    title: 'The PC Engine and the Forgotten Console',
    subtitle: 'How NEC and Hudson Soft built the third most successful console of its era and still lost — and why it matters anyway',
    category: 'history',
    summary: 'The PC Engine dominated Japan in 1988 and 1989, had the first CD-ROM add-on for a game console, and launched in North America as the TurboGrafx-16 in 1989. Almost nobody there bought one. The story of why is the story of how console markets work.',
