    id: 'shoot-em-up-grammar',
    title: 'The Shoot-em-up\'s Grammar',
    subtitle: 'Wave patterns, power-up systems, bullet curtains, and what forty years of shmup design discovered about the relationship between control and chaos',
    category: 'design',
    summary: 'The shoot-em-up is gaming\'s oldest surviving genre. From Space Invaders to DoDonPachi, the basic elements — shoot, dodge, destroy — remained constant while the design vocabulary that organised them grew into one of gaming\'s most sophisticated design traditions.',
